<br>
We were both in Kael, we both decided to duo while we waited for the guild to come in force in pursue of Idol and AoW. We both summoned our PoP pet, he got his water pet and I got my 62 warder up. We thought we could try out the captain bank. Well what in the heck? I, of course, pulled the Captain B and 1 add. Killed the add, then went to the Captain, then we both noticed, the captain was ignoring both of us and was trying to hammer down the mage's pet. <br>
<br>
After Captain Bvellos died, we thought it was kind of odd, and could be those 2 pets agro rule thing goin on, so to verify, I pulled a green giant and let the mage pet tanked in, but not my warder this time, the mage, with courage, stepped right by the giant, not by a splitting second, the giant never turned against the mage. It was very surprising. I also tried it on myself, I pulled another green con'ed giant with a cheap nuke, let my warder tank, I stepped in, again, the giant ignores me and want my warder to be his supper, but alas, the warder had the giant for supper.<br>
<br>
We dont know why or how or what they did, but I do know the pet agro managment is changed. Any of you guys notice any of this?<br>
<br>
