<br>
A pet traditionally cannot take agro away from a character with Active agro if they are in melee range.  I'm assuming that the reason rogues are able to avoid agro is because of evade, but I can't be sure.  I would expect the mob to turn on them on their very next attack after evading though, and reports above seem to indicate that this isn't happening.<br>
<br>
Modrodforsale also mentions pulling with malosini, which should certainly cause Active agro, so perhaps something has changed recently. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=doomteddy>Doomteddy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(1/31/03 9:03:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=972.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Same thing happened to me</span><hr size=1> It seem that it's happening as if pet were a warrior building agro and can keep agro. It is not like those agro that mobs were always on pet (When the AoW/Charm/Pet agro nerf 2 years ago.) Post the pet agro nerf, it would always go for a player, no matter how much the pet been meleeing and anyone run by, the mob will turn and hit that player that just ran by.<br>
<br>
Now this one is different. I pulled a green, stick warder in, jump in and melee, eventually the giant turns away from me and started to focus on my warder. <br>
<br>
That is what I am noticing of this change. I like this kind of pet agro thing, and that is the way it --SHOULD'VE-- been at the FIRST place after the pet agro nerf. Not when a player agro come first, even if pet has built some agro, the mob should've sticked on with the pet. It is just not right when pet/warder agro doesnt work. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Unfortunely I do not know if it's bugged or a confirm changed that forgotten to be said in the patch message.<br>
<br>
I do know that the pet/warder agro has been changed. In a weird way.<br>
